      <title>How To Study The Bible Advice Number 9</title>
      <link>http://tgoodenough1.multiply.com/journal/item/6/How_To_Study_The_Bible_Advice_Number_9</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello my friend, I'll assist you to understand how to study the Bible. We ought to use dictionaries. Take heed that the term is in the plural form, "dictionaries".&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;There is our ordinary dictionary, even as the American Heritage Dictionary. Ordinary dictionaries are acceptable and useful. We ought to put them to use. But to truly comprehend a term, we must get into an etymology dictionary.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Etymology" means tracing the beginning of a word's meaning. Some words are put together from several smaller words, known as "root words". The etymology shows, to us, the meanings of each of the root words. Some etymologies may have to be changed, when newly discovered knowledge comes up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;For example, the Online Etymology Dictionary, at etymonline.com, has normally great etymologies. However, for the word, "abraxas" I learned that Wikipedia had a better etymology, than has the Online Etymology Dictionary. For some words other sources are superior.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;During the time, when you are learning how to study t...&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/timmys-site/Timmys_Site-How_To_Study_The_Bible_Advice_Number_9.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
